'''''Adam and Steve''''' is a [[2005 in film|2005]] [[film]] directed by [[Craig Chester]]. It deals with the lives of two [[homosexuality|gay]] men. The movie had its [[United Kingdom|UK]] premier on [[November 19]] at the [[Cardiff Screen Festival]].

The phrase "Adam and Steve" originated from the common Judeo-Christian argument against homosexuality, in which theologians point out that the natural way of life illustrated by the Biblical account of creation is one between a man and a woman, or "[[Adam and Eve]]," not between a man and a man, or "Adam and Steve."

